[
  {
    "startTime": 0.35,
    "endTime": 6.859,
    "text": "Sometimes a friend will do something exciting and you'll want to be able to ask them how it went."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 6.86,
    "endTime": 13.72,
    "text": "In this video we're going to look at 5 different ways that you can ask someone how something went in English."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 18.22,
    "endTime": 24.43,
    "text": "The first and simplest way to ask somebody in English how things have gone is to say:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 24.43,
    "endTime": 26.18,
    "text": "How did it go?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 26.18,
    "endTime": 28.9,
    "text": "And the faster version would be:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 28.9,
    "endTime": 29.75,
    "text": "How'd it go?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 29.75,
    "endTime": 33.21,
    "text": "Imagine you have a friend who just started a new job."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 33.21,
    "endTime": 36.51,
    "text": "And they've just finished their first day of work."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 36.51,
    "endTime": 37.678,
    "text": "You could ask them:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 37.679,
    "endTime": 38.89,
    "text": "How did it go?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 38.89,
    "endTime": 39.89,
    "text": "Or:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 39.89,
    "endTime": 41.1,
    "text": "How'd it go?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 41.1,
    "endTime": 42.480000000000004,
    "text": "And they could respond with:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 42.48,
    "endTime": 43.967999999999996,
    "text": "It went very well."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 43.969,
    "endTime": 47.550000000000004,
    "text": "Or, it didn't go so well."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 47.55,
    "endTime": 53.68,
    "text": "The second way that you could ask someone how something went is to say:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 53.69,
    "endTime": 54.659,
    "text": "How did that go?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 54.659,
    "endTime": 56.42,
    "text": "Or, the faster version:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 56.42,
    "endTime": 58.389,
    "text": "How'd that go?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 58.389,
    "endTime": 64.43900000000001,
    "text": "Imagine someone has told you that they just used a new recipe to cook a chicken."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 64.438,
    "endTime": 65.438,
    "text": "You could say:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 65.438,
    "endTime": 68.0,
    "text": "Hey Dave, how did that go?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 68.0,
    "endTime": 69.68,
    "text": "And they could respond with:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 69.68,
    "endTime": 70.68,
    "text": "It went very well."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 70.68,
    "endTime": 72.60000000000001,
    "text": "The chicken was delicious."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 72.6,
    "endTime": 73.63,
    "text": "Or:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 73.63,
    "endTime": 74.82,
    "text": "It didn't go well."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 74.82,
    "endTime": 76.589,
    "text": "I burnt the chicken."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 76.59,
    "endTime": 83.34,
    "text": "A third way to ask someone how something went is to ask the question:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 83.34,
    "endTime": 86.28,
    "text": "How was that? or How was it?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 86.28,
    "endTime": 89.93900000000001,
    "text": "Maybe you have a friend that just told that they went scuba diving."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 89.939,
    "endTime": 93.669,
    "text": "A way to ask them how it went would be to say:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 93.67,
    "endTime": 96.14,
    "text": "How was it? or How was that?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 96.14,
    "endTime": 98.469,
    "text": "They could be used interchangeably."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 98.469,
    "endTime": 99.52,
    "text": "You could say:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 99.52,
    "endTime": 100.789,
    "text": "How was it Dave?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 100.789,
    "endTime": 102.9,
    "text": "And they could respond:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 102.9,
    "endTime": 103.2,
    "text": "It was amazing."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 103.2,
    "endTime": 105.619,
    "text": "I saw so many fish."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 105.619,
    "endTime": 106.939,
    "text": "Or they might say:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 106.939,
    "endTime": 108.619,
    "text": "It didn't go very well."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 108.619,
    "endTime": 110.659,
    "text": "I'm afraid of the water."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 110.659,
    "endTime": 116.55000000000001,
    "text": "A fourth way to ask someone how something went is to ask the question:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 116.55,
    "endTime": 118.19,
    "text": "How did things turn out?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 118.19,
    "endTime": 122.35,
    "text": "Imagine a friend has borrowed money from you to start a business."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 122.35,
    "endTime": 124.649,
    "text": "When you see them you could say:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 124.649,
    "endTime": 126.52,
    "text": "How did things turn out?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 126.52,
    "endTime": 128.62,
    "text": "And they could respond by saying:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 128.62,
    "endTime": 130.44,
    "text": "Things are going very well."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 130.44,
    "endTime": 132.59,
    "text": "Here is your money back."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 132.59,
    "endTime": 134.44,
    "text": "Or they might say:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 134.44,
    "endTime": 136.359,
    "text": "Things aren't going so great."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 136.36,
    "endTime": 139.69000000000003,
    "text": "I won't be able to pay you back for several weeks."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 139.69,
    "endTime": 146.49,
    "text": "A fifth and final way to ask someone how something went is to ask the question:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 146.49,
    "endTime": 148.55,
    "text": "How did you make out?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 148.55,
    "endTime": 150.8,
    "text": "And the faster version would be:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 150.8,
    "endTime": 153.70000000000002,
    "text": "How didja make out?  **Not proper written English, but is used in spoken English."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 153.7,
    "endTime": 154.6,
    "text": "Or:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 154.7,
    "endTime": 155.92,
    "text": "Howdya make out?  **Not proper written English, but is used in spoken English."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 155.92,
    "endTime": 157.5,
    "text": "How did you make out?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 157.5,
    "endTime": 158.86,
    "text": "How didja make out?  **Not proper written English, but is used in spoken English."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 158.86,
    "endTime": 161.60000000000002,
    "text": "Or, Howdya make out?  **Not proper written English, but is used in spoken English."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 161.6,
    "endTime": 165.2,
    "text": "Imagine you have a friend who recently took a driving test."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 165.2,
    "endTime": 166.6,
    "text": "You could say to them:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 166.6,
    "endTime": 169.38,
    "text": "Hey, how did you make out?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 169.38,
    "endTime": 171.4,
    "text": "And they could respond by saying:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 171.4,
    "endTime": 173.1,
    "text": "It went super good."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 173.1,
    "endTime": 174.239,
    "text": "I passed."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 174.24,
    "endTime": 176.14000000000001,
    "text": "Or, maybe they'll say:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 176.14,
    "endTime": 177.44,
    "text": "It didn't' go so well."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 177.44,
    "endTime": 179.29,
    "text": "I hit a tree."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 179.29,
    "endTime": 183.10899999999998,
    "text": "Well that was 5 ways to ask someone how something went in the past."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 183.11,
    "endTime": 189.60000000000002,
